summary: I don’t like photos of myself, but this one is really good. Little kid with a comic book (I am 22 but I look younger). Reading...
caption: I don’t like photos of myself, but this one is really good. Little kid with a comic book (I am 22 but I look younger). Reading is one of my favourite ways to escape from reality, to feel better. (Besides watching movies with Johnny Depp, of course) I have a lot on my head right now, but when I have a comic book in my hands, I feel like troubles fade away and it is just me and my favourite heroes. I just wanted to share it with you.

title: Hello Tumblr Universe.
body:
It’s been a very long time since I’ve been on this site, it was a site I once used to adore and obviously still do.

Unfortunately my writing had to come to an end about two years back due to some mental health issues that I won’t bore you with. I deleted my old page so this is me starting from a fresh new page and a brand new place in my life.

As always, I will always take in any requests any of my readers send in, as it is rare that I won’t know a fandom even slightly.

So, to my new page with currently 0 followers, I’ve come home.

Love always,

Luna xo

summary: Title: Piece of Silly Affection Summary: Steve looked good, He looked hale and hearty and uninjured in his leather jacket,...
body:
Title: Piece of Silly Affection

Summary: Steve looked good, He looked hale and hearty and uninjured in his leather jacket, too-tight shirt, and jeans. He got off the motorcycle and his movements were graceful and fluid - no obvious signs of injury. He took off his helmet and –

Oh.

Steve had a beard.

Bucky’s mechanical hand spasmed oddly.

Word count: 12k

Rating: PG-13
